overview.Title: Overview
overview.Copy: <p>Sika Limited is a wholly owned subsidiary of Sika AG, a global company based in Switzerland specialising in the manufacture and supply of chemical based products for construction and industry. A world-leader in its field Sika has 124 production and marketing subsidiaries in 80 countries, generates annual sales of CHF 4.8 billion and is committed to providing quality, service, safety and environmental care.</p><p>In the UK, Sika provides market-leading solutions for flooring, sealing and bonding applications, waterproofing, roofing, structural sealing and strengthening and many other construction applications.</p><p>Sika&rsquo;s head office is based in Welwyn Garden City and has offices in Norwich and Preston.</p>

history.Title: History
history.Copy: <p>In 2010, Sika celebrated its 100-year anniversary. Developing innovative products and solutions and being consistent towards all stakeholders have made it possible for Sika to grow throughout its first century.</p><p>We are now present in over 80 countries, with over 15,300 employees with sales of CHF 4,829 million (2012).</p><p>Principles of sustainable development play a decisive role at Sika because these principles answer to todays and tomorrows challenges. The challenges are driven by megatrends such as water management, energy conservation or climate protection, all of which will shape future economic conditions and growth. Entrepreneurial success depends on intelligent solutions matched to these megatrends.</p>

brands.Title: Brands
brands.Copy: <p>Sika is a pioneer in technological innovations designed to meet global challenges. Sika's UK business is aligned into seven different target markets, these being: Concrete, Waterproofing, Roofing, Flooring, Sealing & Bonding, Refurbishment and Industry.</p><p>For each of these market Sika has brands that combine high performance with proven track record and versatility. This includes its renown Sika 1 below ground waterproofing system; ComfortFloor its innovative flooring system; Sika Monotop concrete repair and Sikafloor car park systems.</p><p>Many products are supported with BBA accreditation and meet all relevant Building Regulations and standards.</p>

locations.Title: Locations
locations.Copy: <p>CFA has a presence in over 80 countries and has over 15,300 employees</p><p>The company has grown continuously since its foundation in 1910. The first subsidiary outside Europe was established as early as 1932 in Japan. The Group was split into regions at an early stage so as to allow the national organizations to capitalize on synergies and set up further companies. The Regions are headed by regional managers and effectively shape the companys management structure. The regional managers are members of Group Management and assume line responsibility for their region. The regional management structures encompass sales functions, production responsibility as well as the marketing and development activities geared to the target markets.</p><p>The start of 2013 saw Sika reduce the number of its geographical regions from six to four (EMEA, North America, Latin America and Asia/Pacific). The new regional breakdown is based on unified economic areas and supply chain structures.</p>
